<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-22T13:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-22T13:30:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4450: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Secretary to President
                                        <persName>Roosevelt</persName></hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Early</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                    Warm Springs, Georgia</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-22T13:30:00-05:00">November 22, 1933—1:30
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Reference your wire of today’s date. I believe the President should
                                not receive the communication as method suggested for transmitting
                                it is not the proper one to be used in the circumstances. I also
                                suggest very confidentially that caution be exercised in dealing
                                with the intermediary mentioned.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                                Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>